Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

All commercial flights have ceased operation to/from Panama until at least 22 May 2020. There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from Panama, but some special flights are currently operating (see below).
If you cannot leave Panama at this time, see information on staying in Panama during coronavirus.
This travel advice will be updated when further departure options become available. Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
Spirit Airlines special flights
Spirit Airlines will be running special flights departing from Panama City, Tocumen International Airport, to Fort Lauderdale, Florida, USA on Friday 15 May and Tuesday 19 May. Passengers with a valid ESTA are qualified for this flight as long as they have been outside one of the designated areas (UK, Republic of Ireland, the Schengen Zone, Iran or China) for more than 14 days. British nationals who have been outside one of these areas can still apply for an ESTA.
Book on the Spirit Airlines website.
There are onward flights to London Heathrow Airport from Miami International Airport. You should coordinate your onward connection to the UK accordingly.
Special European flight
There is a special European flight, operated by Evelop Air, from Panama Tocumen International Airport to Paris Charles de Gaulle Airport on Monday 11 May at 2pm. It will make a 90 minute stop in Honduras (San Pedro Sula) to pick up other passengers. Passengers that have boarded the flight in Panama will not be allowed to disembark the plane in Honduras. Arrival in Paris is scheduled for 10:30am Tuesday 12 May.
Booking for this flight has now closed. The British Embassy is not aware of any other special humanitarian flights leaving from Panama City to mainland Europe. There are no plans currently for direct flights to the UK.
Transport to the airport for this flight
Taxis, Cabify and InDriver continue to operate, as do the two transport options below. Others may be available. You should book in advance and inform the British Embassy of your arrangements, as below:
